product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:1:# PIP — Mini Game Flow
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:3:**Status:** Current Approved Game Flow + Daily Soft Reward Decay Proposal  
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:4:**Scope:** Mini Game screens and in-game behavior only  
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:6:**Design Source of Truth:** `Sprint & Mock - Design System.html`
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:12:This document defines only the playable Mini Game experience:
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:14:- Mini Game Main Entry / Stage Path
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:22:- Navigation inside Mini Game
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:24:This document may describe reward values only when they directly affect Mini Game UI state, button labels, and post-Attempt flow.
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:28:- VIP pricing
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:35:- Ad placement outside the Mini Game reward choice
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:36:- Server-side reward economy outside this Mini Game flow
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:38:Those rules belong in the external reward, VIP, inventory, and monetization documents.
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:44:Mini Game is a separate mode from Practice.
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:46:- Do not present Mini Game as inside Practice.
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:47:- Use `Mini Game Main Entry` as the neutral parent screen until final app navigation is approved.
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:49:- Mini Game is designed as a short, repeatable, stage-based learning loop.
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:50:- Mini Game must not block learning progress with forced ads or energy-style wait timers.
product_bible/01_game_flow/mini_game_flow.md:54:## 3. Mini Game Main Entry / Stage Path
